    Split decision
    Milan: Italy rsquo;s top-flight Serie A clubs confirmed they will split from the second division Serie B sides in an attempt to make up ground on England rsquo;s Premier League and Spain rsquo;s La Liga. The leagues will split from the start of the 2010-11 season and means the Serie A sides will no longer have to pay any money to their Serie B counterparts.
    Late catch
